In LESS, any class works as a mix-in, so `icons.less` could be modified to work as mixins quite easily - in fact, it's just a syntax tweak away, so this:

    @{fa-css-prefix}-check:before { content: @fa-var-check; }

Becomes that:

    @{fa-css-prefix}-check { &:before { content: @fa-var-check; } }

This would enable you to create more semantic CSS rules, e.g. using `import (reference)` for the font-awesome files, so that you get only the properties and CSS rules that are actually in use in your stylesheet, rather than embedding the whole library.

